**What is the current behavior?**

how to find out where inline style come from

init a create react app project, or check out this demo repo `https://github.com/craigcosmo/my-app1.git`

create a simple component 
```js
// body component
import React from 'react';

const css ={
	bar :{
		backgroundColor:'red',
	}
}
function App() {
	return (
		<div style={css.bar}>
			ss
		</div>
	);
}

export default App;

```
run the app, inspect the style in dev tool. you see some thing like his

<img width="1394" alt="Screen_Shot_2019-06-22_at_2_10_53_AM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/538657/59946070-a8867c00-9493-11e9-9d75-c6f894ec203d.png">


There should be an indicator where that style come from, so we can debug it if it was written by some one else

**What is the expected behavior?**

There should  be an indicator show which file/component where the style come from




